  "datePublished": "2025-12-31",
  "description": "An identity element is the \u0026ldquo;do nothing\u0026rdquo; element of an algebraic operation — the element that, when combined with any other element, leaves it unchanged. For addition, the identity is 0: a+0=aa + 0 = a for all aa. For multiplication, the identity is 1: a×1=aa \\times 1 = a for all aa. For string concatenation, the identity is the empty string: appending nothing to a string leaves it as it was. For function composition, the identity is the identity function id(x)=x\\mathrm{id}(x) = x: composing any function with the identity function gives the same function back.\n",
  "name": "Identity Element",
